<TITLE> Bangladesh, German trade rises 'fourfold' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com)  The volume of trade between Germany and Bangladesh has increased fourfold in the last decade, according to the commerce ministry. Commerce minister Faruq Khan received German ambassador Holger Michael on Monday. Khan sought assistance and investment from Germany in renewable energy and river dredging sectors, a statement of the ministry of commerce said. The minister also showed interest in utilising the experience of and advice from German in shipbuilding and textile sectors. Michael mentioned Germany as the second largest export market of Bangladesh and said the volume of trade between his country and Bangladesh increased fourfold in the last decade. He said trade between the two countries had potential to grow further. Michael also expressed Germany's positive stance in investing in Bangladesh. Bangladesh exported and imported products worth US $681.44million and 168.73 million respectively in 2001-02. The figures rose to $2269.75 million and $410.44 million respectively by 2008-09. Bangladesh chiefly exports garments, home textiles, shrimp, leather and leather-made goods, pharmaceuticals, ceramics and jute products to Germany. b
